    public class Count

      • onGroup

        public java.lang.Integer onGroup(Group g)
        onGroup is a visitor that takes a group object and returns the number of unique shapes within the group. groupCount is initialized at 0, then incremented by the return value of each of the individual shapes in the list of shapes within group g. The for loop visits each shape in the list of group g, and returns their distinct counts to be added. If the shape in the group g is itself a group, it recursively calls itself until an integer is returned
        Specified by:
        onGroup in interface Visitor<java.lang.Integer>
        Parameters:
        g - is the group that has its shape count returned
        Returns:
        integer number of shapes within g, groupCount
